  "aboutText": "Rhaphidophora korthalsii is a famous shingling climbing aroid native to humid tropical forests from Thailand to Malesia and the western Pacific. In its juvenile stage, it is a shingling climber with overlapping, closely appressed, matte to slightly glossy leaves pressed flat against a vertical tree trunk or support. As it matures, the leaves transition to a larger, dissected, pinnate form. Stems are robust and attach tightly to their host trees using adhesive roots.",
